OL,6,FMr Clark said NOS became a cult where
OL,7,Fmembers were encouraged to separate
OL,8,Fthemselves from their families and
OL,9,Ffriends.
OL,11,FThey became "dependent" on NOS and
OL,12,F"desperate for the attention and
OL,13,Fpraise" of its leader, he said.
OL,15,F"They were encouraged to give up their
OL,16,Ftime, finances and, eventually, their
OL,17,Fsense of self to this organisation and
OL,18,Fits leader," Mr Clark said.
