OL,6,F"The defendant was seen by a number of
OL,7,Fwitnesses to be surrounded by
OL,8,Fattractive women at his home," Mr
OL,9,FClark told jurors.
OL,11,F"They were noted to be wearing
OL,12,Flingerie or otherwise revealing
OL,13,Fclothing whilst apparently employed to
OL,14,Flook after the needs of the defendant."
OL,16,FThe prosecutor said that Brain would
OL,17,F"suddenly appear" in the lives of
OL,18,Ffemale members of NOS, "often picking
OL,19,Fthem up in his car whilst they were
OL,20,Fwalking along".
