OL,4,Cnumber' of women, court told
OL,6,F"It is the Crown's case that the women
OL,7,Fnamed on the indictment who were
OL,8,Finvolved in sexual acts with the
OL,9,Fdefendant did not consent to those
OL,10,Facts," Mr Clark said.
OL,12,F"Any capacity they had to consent had
OL,13,Fbeen removed by the domineering nature
OL,14,Fof the defendant, by his control over
OL,15,Ftheir entire lives and by their
OL,16,Fabsolute terror of being ostracised
OL,17,Fand that's what he intended.
