OL,4,Cnumber' of women, court told
OL,6,F"It is the Crown's case that the
OL,7,Fcomplainants in this case either
OL,8,Fexpressly made it clear that they did
OL,9,Fnot consent to the sexual acts with
OL,10,Fwhich the defendant is accused or that
OL,11,Fthere was no real legal consent due to
OL,12,Fthe cult-like domineering nature of
OL,13,Fthe defendant's control over them.
OL,15,F"At best, many of the complainants in
OL,16,Fthis case the Crown say merely
OL,17,Fsubmitted to the defendant's actions
OL,18,Fbut they did not, in law, consent to
OL,19,Fthem. Their will had been overborne."
